lead_paragraph: Centre Seta Tamanivalu and fullback Damian McKenzie scored two tries each as Waikato Chiefs kept up their chase for the top spot in Super Rugby with a 50-5 demolition of the Queensland Reds at Lang Park in Brisbane on Friday.

headline.print_headline: Tamanivalu, McKenzie Grab Two Tries Each as Chiefs Thrash Reds
headline.main: Tamanivalu, McKenzie Grab Two Tries Each as Chiefs Thrash Reds
